# Document Map

## Purpose

This repository uses a documentation-first structure. Each major document exists for a distinct reason.

## Documents

- `README.md`: quick orientation and project summary
- `AGENTS.md`: repository collaboration rules for agent workflows
- `CLAUDE.md`: Claude Code-specific adaptation notes
- `docs/README.md`: entry index for the documentation system
- `docs/domain-overview.md`: domain language and scope summary
- `docs/architecture.md`: high-level repository and system shape
- `docs/code-style-guide.md`: code, writing, and change-style expectations
- `docs/doc-templates.md`: reusable templates for recurring documents
- `docs/roadmap.md`: staged direction and planned maturation
- `docs/constraints.md`: boundaries, assumptions, and explicit non-goals
- `docs/repo-workflow-guide.md`: branch, commit, and Jira/workflow rules
- `docs/task-delivery-guide.md`: what documentation each task should leave behind
- `docs/task-execution-template.md`: execution order and pre-commit checks
- `docs/legacy-reshape-guide.md`: reshape flow for an existing repository
- `docs/legacy-structure-inventory.md`: current-state map before restructuring docs
- `docs/{{release_version}}/features/`: version-specific feature notes and review checklists

## Rule

If a document does not have a distinct purpose, it should not be added.
